<strong>Incoming Folder & Sorting</strong><br /><br />Alphabetical sorting is still not working properly:<br />1. Folders beginning by a number.<br />2. Files beginning with numbers.<br />3. The rest of folders.<br />4. The rest of files.<br />Of course folders should be first, files later.<br /><br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />I have 3 files (file1, file2, file3) in incoming folder and I have somewhere folders "music" and "books", NeoLoader will show: books, file1, file2, file3, music. I want it to show: books, incoming, music.<br />anyone to second that request?<br /></div></blockquote><br />It's unintuitive. In eMule you can display "All files" one-by-one, or files in catalogs (folder tree); Shareaza for example displays files in catalogs. But your program displays catalogs, AND files from Incoming folder! Incoming folder should be treated as any other folder (and pinned to the top of list and expanded if no other folders exists), am I right?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forum.neoloader.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3790">Zebra</a> — Tue Feb 17, 2015 9:10 pm</p><hr />
