<content type="html" xml:base="http://forum.neoloader.com/viewtopic.php?t=3484&amp;p=17787#p17787"><![CDATA[
<blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />What is wrong with ed2k magnet links?<br /></div></blockquote><br />emule dont support it those no one will use it<br /><br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />Why don't make one common link standard for all P2P protocols?<br /></div></blockquote><br />I did its a Neo link <img class="smilies" src="http://forum.neoloader.com/images/smilies/biggrin.png" alt=":D" title=":D" /><br /><br />Practically the only difference between a neo link and a extended magnet link is that it has the link.neoloader.to perpended<br /><br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />At least please accept incorrect "urn:ed2khash" magnets...<br /></div></blockquote><br />no particular reason, i can ad that to the next release, i did not knew shareaza does that<br /><br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />The download speed doesn't depend on the network you're using, in fact eDonkey/Kad should be faster than BitTorrent because of its sophisticated credit/queue system<br /></div></blockquote><br />The credit/queue system is everything but sophisticated, it is a fucked up attempt to leech of casual users and keep the gross of the upload bandwidth for the elite that can afford to run their donkeys 24/7!<br /><br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />The whole idea of BitTorrent network is sick: 2 identical files have different hashes!<br /></div></blockquote><br />That is indeed sick for a filesharing system, but actually its very smart for a content distribution system and, well BT was not designed for filesharing but for content distribution.<br /><br /><br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />BT is not searchable by itself, I don't count external network like NeoShare.<br /></div></blockquote><br />Technically speaking eMules kad is to the same extent a external network to ed2k, as neokad is to bittorent.<br /><br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />Multifiles (?) - use .zip archives,<br /></div></blockquote><br />zip is a shit if you want to share your music collection, as than you need to have you music twice on your HDD, once as zip and once in a usable for you format.<br />With a torrent you can share each album or each discography as a multifile without the need to waste HDD space.<br /><br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />There is a similar thing for .emulecollections - metalinks, why it's not used in any P2P program?<br /></div></blockquote><br />metalinks?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forum.neoloader.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=561">DavidXanatos</a> — Thu Nov 13, 2014 12:51 pm</p><hr />
