<content type="html" xml:base="http://forum.neoloader.com/viewtopic.php?t=3484&amp;p=17785#p17785"><![CDATA[
<blockquote><div><cite>Zebra wrote:</cite><br />The download speed doesn't depend on the network you're using, in fact eDonkey/Kad should be faster than BitTorrent because of its sophisticated credit/queue system. The whole idea of BitTorrent network is sick: 2 identical files have different hashes! BT is not searchable by itself, I don't count external network like NeoShare. Multifiles (?) - use .zip archives, or .emulecollections! There is a similar thing for .emulecollections - metalinks, why it's not used in any P2P program? I hope the guy who invented BitTorrent will die with pain...<br /><br />Why people are so brainless? Why the worst ever filesharing network is the most popular, while such awesome network(s) like Gnutella(with DHT) with no central servers, normal hashing (no, different hashes for identical files aren't normal), integrated search and variable piece size is dying?<br /></div></blockquote><br /><br />Yes, the download speed depends also from the network that you're using. I can tell you stupid example that is: Download the file X from BitTorrent and from ed2k, tell me which is faster. But by the way I expalin you why it is faster:<br />- Torrent doesn't have the credit/queque system (and no, emule's system is not sophisticated at all lol)<br />- Torrent doesn't have the 3kb/s slot limit<br />- Torrent doesn't need to transfer 9 Mb before another peer can start uploading datas<br />- Using well know BT websites searching a torrent u have more information, know the release of new files and fakes are very rare<br /><br />Why should I use .zip archives ? With multifile people can choose what they want download and what not.<br />Why should I use .emulecollection ? I don't want to share an additional file for share a discography for example.<br />Why people are so brainless? They aren't, they just don't want to wait days with PC on to download something while can be downloaded in some minutes with another software...<br /><br />For the reasons above it is obviously diying.<br /><br />Would you like to talk also about that most of the torrent clients work on any platform, even android while the only emule's alternative its aMule ?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forum.neoloader.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2495">Neo26</a> — Thu Nov 13, 2014 11:48 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
